  "prompt": "Can European citizens live and work in the Bahamas?",
  "response": "Generally, European citizens do not have automatic rights to live and work in the Bahamas. To live and work in the Bahamas, non-Bahamian citizens, including Europeans, typically need to:\n\n1. Obtain a work permit from the Bahamian government\n2. Have a job offer from a Bahamian employer\n3. Meet specific immigration requirements\n4. Apply for the appropriate visa or residence permit\n\nThe process can be complex and depends on factors like:\n- The type of work\n- Length of intended stay\n- Specific employment circumstances\n- Individual qualifications\n\nEuropean citizens interested in living and working in the Bahamas should contact the Bahamian embassy or consulate in their home country for current, detailed information about immigration and work regulations.",
